Nollywood actor and filmmaker, Alesh Sanni has said Yoruba movies gives more fame. The crossover actor, who started his career in 2012 under the tutelage of Dele Ogundipe, made this known in a brief chat with The Nation.   Lady Donli: Sacrifice I made for my music     Onos Morgan goes for gold in Italy     International Women’s Day: Genevieve, Kate Henshaw, 38…   “ I have seen the Yoruba movie industry and I like it because it gives more fame but I don’t do everything for fame. I don’t want fame without money so I had to step up and mingle around everything and see which one is better so I’m doing both,” he said. The actor who doubles as an entrepreneur and medical technician in the USA has produced over thirteen movies including the latest movie; ‘Rancor’.